LAGOS – The operatives of Ogun State police command have arrested three persons on allegation that they vandalised MTN mast. They were arrested on Saturday, August 18, 2018, in Atan, Ota area of Adodo Ota local government of Ogun State. The suspects were identified as kehinde Yahaya, 36-year-old, Akeem Adetona, also 36-year-old and Taofeek Olalere. They were arrested following a distress call made to the Divisional Police Officer (DPO), Atan Ota, SP Abiodun Salau. Daily Independent gathered that the call was made about 12 midnight by the vigilante men at Onigbogbo Phase 2, that a group of thieves had burgled into the MTN mast and were carting away 12 solar power panels valued at about N14million. Abimbola Oyeyemi, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the state who confirmed the arrest said on the strength of the distress call, the DPO led his patrol men to the scene where three of the hoodlums were arrested while others escaped into the nearby bush. Oyeyemi, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP) said 12 solar panels as well as their operational Danfo bus with registration number Lagos LND 10 XE were recovered from the suspects. Meanwhile, the commissioner of police CP Ahmed Iliyasu has ordered the immediate transfer of the suspects to the Federal Special Anti-Robbery Squad (FSARS), for discreet investigation. The CP equally directed that serious manhunt should be launched to arrest other fleeing members of the gang with the view to bringing them to justice. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 